org.cef.handler

Interface CefResourceHandler

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CefResourceHandlerAdapter 

    public interface CefResourceHandler
    Implement this interface to handle custom resource requests. This interface is a "new" API and an old API in one: the deprecated methods are part of the old API. The new API allows for parallel processing of requests, because it does not channel all reads through a dedicated IO thread, and it allows for skipping of bytes as part of handling Range requests.(${t_45ef62b5dbc143808979320275827fbe})

      • getResponseHeaders

        void getResponseHeaders(CefResponse response,
                        IntRef responseLength,
                        StringRef redirectUrl)
        Retrieve response header information. If the response length is not known set |responseLength| to -1 and readResponse() will be called until it returns false. If the response length is known set |responseLength| to a positive value and readResponse() will be called until it returns false or the specified number of bytes have been read. Use the |response| object to set the mime type, http status code and other optional header values.(${t_a8e1fd1454df455b811ffe502fd9b161})
        Parameters:
        response - The request response that should be returned. Instance only valid within the scope of this method.(${t_6e2bea18c1b543cb829288b2b0798e0b})
        responseLength - Optionally set the response length if known.(${t_fcd1965b87034d6db68745a37bed8f7e})
        redirectUrl - Optionally redirect the request to a new URL.(${t_1d044c912da141c39a5075ea449f32e6})

      • open

        boolean open(CefRequest request,
             BoolRef handleRequest,
             CefCallback callback)
        Open the response stream. This and related (getResponseHeaders, read, skip) methods will be called in sequence but not from a dedicated thread.

        For backwards compatibility set |handleRequest| to false and return false and the processRequest() method will be called.

        (${t_f5b5441f6af24ffd8613c9bc7e7edc09})
        Parameters:
        request - The request itself. Cannot be modified in this callback. Instance only valid within the scope of this method.(${t_9d93000e26b14bb8b52b93cfad1dfb2e})
        handleRequest - Set to true to handle/cancel the request immediately(${t_ae75479c6e584161b01eaa4686969d1f})
        callback - Callback to continue or cancel the request at a later time(${t_6212d0dda4e048f39421fcbdb96eb16f})
        Returns:
        True to handle the request(${t_34d604e79a3a4b53a093ea0e10f6306a})

      • read

        boolean read(byte[] dataOut,
             int bytesToRead,
             IntRef bytesRead,
             CefResourceReadCallback callback)
        Read response data. If data is available immediately copy up to |bytesToRead| bytes into |dataOut|, set |bytesRead| to the number of bytes copied, and return true. To read the data at a later time store |dataOut|, set |bytesRead| to 0, return true and call the callback when the data is available. To indicate response completion set |bytesRead| to 0 and return false. To indicate failure set |bytesRead| to <0 (e.g. -2 for ERR_FAILED) and return false.

        For backwards compatibility set |bytesRead| to -1 and return false and the readResponse() method will be called.

        (${t_4666bc9c5ac945a9a56bf219b06a733b})
        Parameters:
        dataOut - Write data to this buffer. Buffer remains valid until either an immediate response is delivered (return true) or the callback is called later when data is available (return false).(${t_14ac969110c84c38810ae15060c84f36})
        bytesToRead - Size of the buffer.(${t_6a62fa51748144f794468c1c0027c293})
        bytesRead - Number of bytes written to the buffer.(${t_959ceec5e57846fcaca6bf165c137bd5})
        callback - Callback to execute if data will be available asynchronously.(${t_b2db115db7e6401591efa96e545073c4})
        Returns:
        True if more data is or will be available.(${t_b9ed4159cd0c40d7bdf393839895e54c})

      • skip

        boolean skip(long bytesToSkip,
             LongRef bytesSkipped,
             CefResourceSkipCallback callback)
        Skip response data when requested by a Range header. Skip over and discard |bytesToSkip| bytes of response data. If data is available immediately set |bytesSkipped| to the number of bytes skipped and return true. To read the data at a later time set |bytesSkipped| to 0, return true and execute |callback| when the data is available. To indicate failure set |bytesSkipped| to < 0 (e.g. -2 for ERR_FAILED) and return false.(${t_db74ca2c0456466eafd1cef194474d39})
        Parameters:
        bytesToSkip - Number of bytes to skip.(${t_2be8a0f6e4d249288b7512d36be0226a})
        bytesSkipped - Number of bytes skipped.(${t_b20bca66cd2648a497a77a64d9b64786})
        callback - Callback to execute if data will be skipped asynchronously.(${t_6dc29c533d864a4d87bc2f682244dc6b})
